HEADWORD: evangel
<hw>e*van"gel</hw> <pr>(⟦esl⟧*v⟦acr⟧n"j⟦ecr⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F. <ets>⟦eacute⟧vangile</ets>, L. <ets>evangelium</ets>, Gr.
<grk>e'yagge`lion</grk> good news, glad tidings, gospel, fr.
<grk>e'ya`ggelos</grk> bringing good news; <grk>e'y^</grk> well +
<grk>'a`ggelein</grk> to bear a message. See <er>Eu-</er>, and
<er>Angel</er> and cf. <er>Evangely</er>.]</ety> <def>Good news;
announcement of glad tidings; especially, the gospel, or a gospel.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Her funeral anthem is a glad <qex>evangel</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Whittier.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

